The paper discusses the development and comparison of various approaches for automatic gender classification using features derived from human bodies and/or behaviors. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it deals with image and video analysis. Additionally, the paper mentions applications of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), computer-aided physiological or psychological analysis (cs.SI), and machine learning (cs.LG) in the context of gender classification. Finally, the paper also discusses social network information-based methods, which could fall under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
